      "node_id": "C_kwDOABII59oAKDk2MzI0NTBmZjY1YzFmZWUyOWMyNTY0YTZhZDY0ZGZhYWQ0ZDY2M2M",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/git/commits/9632450ff65c1fee29c2564a6ad64dfaad4d663c",
      "actor": null,
      "commit_id": null,
      "commit_url": null,
      "created_at": null,
      "html_url": "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/commit/9632450ff65c1fee29c2564a6ad64dfaad4d663c",
      "tree": {
        "sha": "95e698933cf82403bdc9b3a95dd4c7a6b5951ba9",
        "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/git/trees/95e698933cf82403bdc9b3a95dd4c7a6b5951ba9"
      },
      "verification": {
        "verified": true,
        "reason": "valid",
        "payload": "tree 95e698933cf82403bdc9b3a95dd4c7a6b5951ba9\nparent 561d072e0590179f1c60bb2784077589812a05bb\nauthor Cory Fields <cory-nospam-@coryfields.com> 1777399236 +0000\ncommitter fanquake <fanquake@gmail.com> 1777618370 +0100\n\nmulti_index: fix compilation failure with boost >= 1.91\n\nThis effectively reverts a3cb309e7c31853f272bffaa65fb6ab0a7cc4083 from PR #30194.\n\nThat PR reduced the multi_index type signatures as recommended upstream, but\nthis is no longer supported as of boost 1.91 because it is no longer necessary.\n1.91 drops support for the pre-c++11 work-arounds that bloated the type\nsignatures to begin with.\n\nThe upstream `BOOST_MULTI_INDEX_ENABLE_MPL_SUPPORT` define is meant to provide\ncompatibility with removed features, but it does not work for this case. Using\n`indexed_by` directly when defining the `multi_index` (as opposed to inheriting\nfrom it) works with all versions, and avoids the use of the back-compat define.\n\nThis is a slight regression when building against boost < 1.91 because the\nbloated type signatures are reintroduced in that case, but it's not significant\nenough to go to the trouble of introducing version detection and ifdefs.\n\nGithub-Pull: #35175\nRebased-From: 0bc9d354dfd8074d1c36a891a69b6585a8775c65\n",
        "signature": "-----BEGIN PGP SIGNATURE-----\n\niQJPBAABCAA5FiEEz7FuIclQ9n+pXlWPLuufXMCVJsEFAmn0TcIbFIAAAAAABAAO\nbWFudTIsMi41KzEuMTIsMCwzAAoJEC7rn1zAlSbBSMIQALx7I0f7n0RPxM3fKZkE\nr6Rur/uu673ChLUswCbyCwo81nXngffDyFGQs2wZ+yq91yfZ31ToCS0FfqmMwAAw\niXMzbrovKlh87xFb4mBaTD7YnF2277+fH+86q/Lo15feCdY5orkbdkkb9fhYjPMD\nTmDNqmXF0aykxMtSn1hXHx6eGsKOgMBeLcrSi4O77n6aFmty9UejhiIujqI5TE15\nZQUoyOUSmInWJPo2J6DUJFavUf9kk5ze3cqbcbaW9BZEAElBWm7Eu4wqJ1DTNT3b\nfK83hx7n7Sw3/YR6nXh7d8tUsFEaKpf3G//ExU3+gYXEeS/ipwn+cysCrwfvpGBe\nCFScBsCEI0/GEvbXZzdcZEDJiSWJnSnv03TK/v+vOvwZPKBx2lCnO5b5ORCnfYiq\n6T9h+8MuQQfu2JrgmLfrzpWSTSigv5c3QaIOvMDQbEaz+7qzC179j4D0u8gv/PNl\nTDDZnAeaRBCyWLb4CcfW4f70t5VFJTblXLgNqe794PgCgiZv2ob0Z7dYOPMoo8WI\n6V20DqrkA5gzbwzZ6uQibFvSQ3Kn+cPCBi7fFrzlGZ2PQUyuhYqYpAU6cj+hJ7b3\nRxOBIRiJooypRQUFQEQLTV44natjAQzmwQM/6tPsKVE8mCCndd80gF+HTaux/0Cp\n/pHuCc84qDSeJio4czMvnm3N\n=8ULA\n-----END PGP SIGNATURE-----"
      },
      "parents": [
        {
          "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/git/commits/561d072e0590179f1c60bb2784077589812a05bb",
          "sha": "561d072e0590179f1c60bb2784077589812a05bb",
          "html_url": "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/commit/561d072e0590179f1c60bb2784077589812a05bb"
        }
      ],
      "message": "multi_index: fix compilation failure with boost >= 1.91\n\nThis effectively reverts a3cb309e7c31853f272bffaa65fb6ab0a7cc4083 from PR #30194.\n\nThat PR reduced the multi_index type signatures as recommended upstream, but\nthis is no longer supported as of boost 1.91 because it is no longer necessary.\n1.91 drops support for the pre-c++11 work-arounds that bloated the type\nsignatures to begin with.\n\nThe upstream `BOOST_MULTI_INDEX_ENABLE_MPL_SUPPORT` define is meant to provide\ncompatibility with removed features, but it does not work for this case. Using\n`indexed_by` directly when defining the `multi_index` (as opposed to inheriting\nfrom it) works with all versions, and avoids the use of the back-compat define.\n\nThis is a slight regression when building against boost < 1.91 because the\nbloated type signatures are reintroduced in that case, but it's not significant\nenough to go to the trouble of introducing version detection and ifdefs.\n\nGithub-Pull: #35175\nRebased-From: 0bc9d354dfd8074d1c36a891a69b6585a8775c65",
